inn1.comm: bowled on a good length around off and middle, defended from the care on the leg side
played back to the bowler from the crease
drifts on to the pads and Guptill goes back to play it through square leg
no duck today, Ryder moves forward and drives the offbreak on the up through cover, timed it superbly
tries to hit it a bit too hard this time and mis-times towards cover
another crisp drive on the front foot but he doesn't beat cover this time

terrific ball first up, a great length just outside off stump and the ball holds its line instead of angling in with the arm, there's good bounce as well. Guptill began to play at it but then stopped his shot
a huge appeal for a caught behind but the umpire says not out. Guptill was squared up by one that pitched on a good length and straightened and bounced, the ball brushed the thigh of the back leg
a second appeal for caught behind but this time he's missed it by a long way

third time lucky for Holder! Guptill reaches outside the off stump and drives away from his body at a fuller ball that seams away from him. He gets an edge through to the keeper. An easier decision for the umpire to make, after he turned down two consecutive appeals
McCullum gives the bowler the charge right away, gets to the pitch of the ball, and smashes it over cover for four
a fuller ball and this time McCullum stays in his crease, presses forward and flays at it, driving the ball powerfully flat over the infield at cover
short of a length with lots of width outside off, Ryder lines it up, gets down on one knee and slaps it over cover for his second boundary
the line is closer to the left-hander this time and Ryder slashes it through point for a single
he's hit that on to the grassy banks behind the deep backward square leg boundary! McCullum swivells and hooks a short of a length ball, making superb connection

over backward point this time! McCullum slashes at a short of a length outside off and the ball sails over the boundary. An overenthusiastic fan tries to catch the ball and falls over the boundary hoarding in the process and on to the field
he's in some mood this afternoon! McCullum charges and drills the ball hard enough to beat mid-on for four more
played into the covers for a single to keep strike
a bouncer and McCullum is ready with the hook and rolls his wrists to keep it down towards deep square leg
that's been pulled flat and far, over the long leg boundary. Ryder is so quick to get into position and latch on to the short of a length ball, swivelling and hitting it hard
tries to hit it too hard through the off side and mis-times it
driven from the crease towards mid-off
that's massive, too full, allowing Ryder to get under it on the front foot and cart it back over the bowler's head with a powerful swing of his arms
driven hard from the crease but can't get it past cover point
McCullum moves back and across in his crease to nudge off his pads through square leg
Ryder played too early at that one and ended up pushing tentatively towards mid-off, New Zealand have screamed to 50
wham! McCullum charges with intent and mows the ball over the deep midwicket boundary. He wasn't to the pitch of the ball but he trusted the bounce on the pitch and absolutely clattered it
defended on he leg side

is there going to be a mix up between the fielders? Charles and Simmons are getting in each others way, and Simmons takes it superbly! McCullum charged and slogged again, but this time he got a top edge and skied the ball high in the region between long on and deep midwicket. Charles was at long on and Simmons was at deep midwicket. They converged on the ball but Simmons called for it in the end and slid as he caught the steepler
played into the covers for a single
driven off the front foot towards long off for a single
played from the crease towards point
Taylor stays in his crease and pushes a delivery towards midwicket
Ryder was making room but got one in the blockhole, he ended up playing it towards extra cover

a huge appeal for a caught behind but the umpire says not out. I think he nicked that. Will West Indies review? They will. Ramdin has asked for it. Taylor stayed back and tries dab the ball late, there's a certain noise as the ball passes the bat. But there's nothing on hotspot. A tricky one for the umpire. It's over to realtime snicko now ... there's a smudge of a noise on real time snicko. What will the third umpire do? Will he overturn the on-field umpire's decision based on the noise and the small spike on real time snicko? He does not. Taylor bats on. Not enough evidence to overturn the decision.
this time Taylor makes neat contact, late-cutting the ball behind point to the boundary
Ryder plonks his foot forward and heaves across the line, placing it behind square
good length and angling into the right-hander, Taylor dabs the ball close on the leg side and runs before Rampaul can prevent the single
a touch slower outside off, Ryder waits for it and uses the width to open the face and let the ball run off the bat past Holder at short third man
short of a length, Ryder is quick to move back and short-arm pull the ball to the deep midwicket boundary
can't bowl that length with these small boundaries, Ryder gets under a short ball and pulls with authority over the deep square leg boundary
there's the yorker from Rampaul, finally. Ryder digs it out on the leg side
driven to long on for a single
Ryder stays in his crease and works the ball through square
Taylor goes deep into his crease and creates the length to cut the ball past the fielder diving to his right at point

Taylor's not hit it as well as Ryder has been! He slogged it from wide outside off stump and ended up mis-hitting it towards wide long-on, where Powell took the catch. He was hitting that against the turn
played off the pads towards square leg
a slower ball, dabbed from the crease close on the leg side
short of a length, slightly slower, Anderson was ready and waiting on the back foot to sit back and pull flat over midwicket for a one-bounce four
pushed uppishly towards mid off, that was quicker from Bravo
a full ball swinging into the blockhole, Ryder gets his legs out of the way and clips it through wide mid-on
I didn't think he timed that perfectly but he still hit it hard enough to clear long-off and bring up his fifty, Ryder cleared his front foot and bashed a length ball down the ground
a full toss on the pads with a hint of swing, Ryder clips it to deep square leg
Ryder drives to long on for two more, Holder cuts it off on the boundary, this is Ryder's fastest ODI fifty
bowled slower outside off, Ryder slogs and misses, that was so close to off stump
played from the crease to short fine leg
a low full toss, clipped off the pads through midwicket
Anderson pulls hard to Rampaul on the edge of the circle at midwicket
played through midwicket for a single this time
strays down leg side, first extra of the innings
that's in the arc and out of the park! Anderson lines it up, takes a long stride forward and slams it over the deep midwicket boundary, that went very far back
cut off the back foot to deep cover
Ryder chips the ball short of he man at long off
Anderson stays back to cut and gets a bottom edge into the ground
Anderson cuts the ball over point and into the gap to run two
cut off the back foot through point
and Anderson sends a full ball screaming to the straight boundary by making room and hitting through the line, hit it all along the ground
poor line and length, short and angling into the left-hander from round the wicket, Anderson swivels and pulls hard to the backward square leg boundary
driven along the ground to long on for a single
a half-volley with width outside off, too easy for Ryder, who square drives between two fielders in the point region
that's a hit-me-please ball, a full toss outside off, Ryder opens the face and drives the ball through point again to find the point boundary
another full toss and Holder is lucky that hasn't disappeared to the boundary too, Ryder drove it to the cover fielder

more massive hitting, Anderson getting down on one knee and carting it over deep square leg with a slog sweep, New Zealand steam ahead. There's $100,000 up for grabs if the six is caught by a person wearing a orange tee shirt with one hand
another one, launched over the wide long off boundary, there's a near collision between two fans trying to take the catch! someone's going to get injured at this rate!
played to cover
that's high and far over deep midwicket again, tremendous slog sweep and it's dropped again in the crowd, no one's catching them one-handed for a $100k
defended from the crease
Anderson has stormed to his fifty in a blaze of muscular hits, he mows this one flat and hard to the deep midwicket boundary, might break a finger if someone in the crowd lays a hand on it
driven into the covers for a single
a full ball outside off, makes room and slices it over point for a single
a short ball and Ryder pulls it to deep midwicket
that's full and wide outside off, but just inside the wide line, the batsman reaches for it but misses
once again Bravo is full and in the blockhole wide outside off, Anderson reaches for it and mis-times towards the bowler
he's hit this one all right, tremendous power behind that shot and Anderson slams a full ball over long off, and another chance is dropped in the crowd
Rampaul bowls a full toss outside off stump, Ryder drives it to deep cover
Anderson is on a rampage, he throws his bat at a full and wide ball outside off and carves it over the deep cover boundary, dropped again by a $100,000 seeking spectator
this is a blur of boundaries now, Anderson gets behind a full and straight ball and hits cleanly through the line, that's just cleared the straight boundary
tremendous! The 100 stand comes off 42 balls, Anderson brings it up by getting on the front foot and hammering it over deep midwicket, it's a small boundary but that's cleared it by plenty
he's running amok, unstoppable. Anderson flicks the ball flat and furiously, watch out in the crowd at deep midwicket, it's heading your way
driven hard but this time the fielder at cover dives and makes the save
driven from the crease to cover, a dot ball!
Anderson slogs across the line and gets a thick bottom edge towards fine leg
a full ball outside off, driven crisply along the ground but he can't beat cover
a low full toss, the yorker gone wrong, Ryder leans into it and drives the ball along the ground into the gap on the cover boundary
too full and too wide outside off, Ryder throws his bat at it, slashing hard, and hits it to the backward point boundary. NZ blaze past 200
the slower ball too far down leg side, that's a wide, Ryder tried to pull that too
Bravo has been battered again, Ryder's simply stood his ground and driven a full ball with fearsome power to the extra cover boundary, these boundaries are small
he's got four! He's going for the fastest century! Anderson slogs across the line and mis-hits it, but still hits it well enough to beat square leg and run to the boundary, along the ground
another one! He was miles away from this short and wide ball, Anderson lunged and threw his bat at it, chopping it over point for a one-bounce four
short of a length and Anderson pulls along the ground to long on
slow, and too short, Ryder waits in his crease, gets down on one knee and pulls the ball to the long-leg boundary, like taking candy from children
Ryder slashes at one outside off and such is his force into the shot that almost loses balance and chips it over point
Anderson gets only a single, tried to pull across the line too hard and inside edged on to his pad

he's done it! A 36-ball ton! Anderson you legend. What a start to 2014. The ball was rubbish, short and around middle and leg, Anderson got inside the line and pulled it miles over the long leg boundary
a full toss this time, carted over the wide long-on boundary, what on earth is going on. My sleep deprived mind can't handle it!
short and wide outside off, Anderson goes forward and then goes back and slaps the ball over cover and into the gap
pulled from the crease to deep midwicket
Ryder now, just pulling away, and there seem to be no fielders anywhere, another one finds the gap on the midwicket boundary
stop the madness! Ryder's down on one knee, and he's swinging for the fences, the ball goes miles over midwicket
hit down the ground for two more, that's paltry, just a two
a slower and full ball on middle stump, Anderson moves across, squares up, and mows the ball to deep square leg
lofted towards wide long off, once bounce to the fielder
a length ball and Ryder simply hits through the line to the straight boundary, he's on 97
a wide full toss, Ryder reaches for it and drives towards deep cover to move to 99
Ryder inside edges a drive to short fine leg to reach his century! He's made a fine comeback to the national side after various problems in 2013
a full ball outside off, driven powerfully along the ground through cover
Bravo lost grip of that slower ball and it ended up as a full toss outside off, Anderson moved towards it and launched it over wide long off
drilled down the ground to long off
Ryder backed away towards leg and Bravo followed him and then tried to scoop it over the keeper, he missed!
lofted towards long-on, reaches the fielder on the first bounce
a full ball outside off, driven along the ground through cover
he's been caught! Ryder's sliced a friendly full toss from outside off stump straight to the man at point. West Indies barely celebrate. They've been hit by a torrent of haymakers this afternoon
Ronchi gives Anderson the strike by scampering a single after failing to make proper contact
a full toss outside off stump, Anderson slashes it towards wide third man and races back for the second
Anderson wanted to hit that towards deep midwicket but closed the face too early, the full toss flew off the leading edge and went towards third man, it fell safely
nudged off the pads towards backward square leg

a full ball angling into the pads, Ronchi flicks towards long leg and then sprints for the second. Corey Anderson has hit the fastest century in ODIs - off 36 balls - to lead NZ to 283 in a 21 over game! Astonishing. What a crackerjack start to 2014.

inn2.comm: good length outside off, Charles stays in his crease and plays towards point
Charles backs away and has a waft at a good length ball that seams away from him, he's beaten

caught by the fielder running in from third man! Charles has a slog at a good length ball, he was aiming to hit down the ground but got a top edge that flew towards third man, Neesham got under it and judged the catch well
a straighter line, Simmons misses the glance and gets hit on the pads for a leg bye
gets behind the line and blocks a good length ball
nudged off the back foot on the leg side for a single
good length with some shape into the right-hander, played from the crease on the leg side
a length ball driven on the up to mid-off for a quick single
short of a length on the hips, the batsman tries to whip it off his body but doesn't make proper contact
Simmons moves outside leg to make room and slogs, he ends up mis-timing it to mid-on
short and wide outside off, angling across the right-hander, Simmons jumps back and lays into it, slashing the ball hard in front of point to the boundary
he charges this time and slogs at a short of a length delivery that slants away from him, he makes no contact
a short-arm jab off the back foot sends the ball along the ground in front of square leg
punched from the crease towards cover
punched from the crease but the ball doesn't beat cover, Mills is keeping it tight, on a good length
that's West Indies' first six! Simmons rocks back, squares up and pulls the short ball over the deep midwicket boundary

that's a terrific shot, Simmons goes back, and punches stylishly with one leg off the ground through extra cover, the batsmen think it's four so the running is lax, but Brendon McCullum is in hot pursuit and he dives full length to prevent the boundary
nudged on the leg side for a single

caught at deep square leg! Superbly held! Simmons pulled a short of a length ball on the front foot and it travelled flat towards deep square leg. Milne came forward and to his left to get to the ball and adjusted well as it swerved and dipped to his right. He ended up catching it low to the ground, sliding as he did so
Powell is off the mark by mis-timing a drive to mid-on
short of a length and pulled, not very well, towards deep square
a short ball and Powell mis-times the pull, the ball lobs short of mid-on, the ball hit high on the bat
falling like skittles, they are! Powell steps out of his crease and flat-bats a short of a length ball straight to mid-off, where Neesham takes it at head height
good length, pitching around off and seaming across, defended on the back foot on the off side
dabbed on the front foot behind point
nudged off the front foot to midwicket
punched off the back foot towards mid-on
moves forward and flicks the ball to midwicket
moves forward and across to nudge the ball in front of square, the fielder from midwicket prevents the single
nudged to midwicket again, can't beat the man
Ryder's bowling off spin, dabbed to short third man
driven on the front foot to long off
nearly in the blockhole from round the wicket, dug out on the off side, NZ hurrying through covers because of weather
played back to the bowler
tries to launch it over cover point but misses
worked off the pads behind square. that over took less than 90 seconds!
nudged off the pads through midwicket, zipping between deliveries
pushed to long on for one more, McCullum's already at the start of his run up
hits the pad and there's a huge appeal for lbw, that looked close, did it pitch outside leg? No review
worked of the front foot towards square
pushed off the front foot towards point, the decide against the single
played back to the bowler
an attempted hoick over the leg side connects with air, the ball goes off the pad on the off side
tries to launch the ball over cover but misses
slightly short, Bravo goes back and drives the ball through midwicket
a full toss outside off, driven on the front foot towards wide long off
driven once again through extra cover for one more
driven gently towards long off, looks like West Indies are banking on the weather now
dropped short and Walton goes back and swivels to pull the ball to the square leg boudnary
played back to the bowler on the back foot
driven on the front foot to long on
bowled full outside leg, plays a half-paddle sweep to fine leg
that's a long hop, Bravo rocks back, gets under it and heaves it over the deep midwicket boundary
nudged off the pads through square
he's edged that I think and the keeper's put it down, he tried to drive at one that angled across him
pushed towards square for a single
played with an open face to point
played off the front foot to midwicket
worked off the pads behind square
lofted towards long on and the ball falls just short of the fielder
Walton goes back and pulls the ball from off stump to deep midwicket
driven from the crease through the gap at cover
goes back and across to tap the ball towards square leg for a single
a full ball on middle stump, flicked in front of square for a single
short ball, but he's mis-timed the pull behind sqquare
defended back to the bowler
a full ball on leg and middle, driven wide of the diving Ryder to long on
a long hop and Walton has pulled it straight to the fielder on the deep square leg boundary, the fielder barely had to move
driven from the crease through cover point, Deonarine is off the mark
Bravo defends back to the bowler
a full toss on the pads and Bravo can't beat midwicket with the flick
cut behind point but the fielder at short third man cuts it off
tries to sweep but misses and is hit on the pad by one that pitches outside leg
nudged off the front foot on the off side
defended from the crease on the leg side. West Indies have shut shop. They are hoping for rain.
played off the front foot on the leg side
driven to long on for a single
driven off the pads to long on
pushed off the front foot towards mid off
played off the front foot behind point
defended on the front foot to the bowler
a full ball outside off, cracked off the front foot but can't beat point, a crisp drive that was
driven fluently again but doesn't cover
driven to wide long off for one more
down leg side, that's a wide
shorter length, hit from the crease through cover
defended on the back foot on the off side

that's a full toss and Bravo has carted it over the deep midwicket boundary, a fan in an orange tee-shirt is getting under the ball with one hand to win $100k but he drops it! Everyone is getting in the catcher's way. They should let one person go for it and share the spoils!
nudged off the pads behind square
flicked off the pads to midwicket
goes back and nudges behind square
beaten outside the off stump
driven on the front foot to mid off
nearly in the blockhole but not quite, Bravo comes forward and plays a cracking cover drive to the boundary
driven on the front foot to cover
a short ball but it's slanting down leg side
moves forward and across to close the face and play to midwicket
a bouncer of a three-pace run-up! the batsman ducks under it
driven from the crease to cover
waits for a full ball and flicks through midwicket
waits in his crease and moves across to flick off his pads behind square
defended on the front foot on the off side
inside edges the drive on to his boot
shorter length, hit with a flat bat to long on
played from the crease to point
short and wide outside off stump, the left-hander gets under it and cracks it over point
good length and straight, defended back to the bowler
goes back and square drives a length ball to deep cover
a full ball outside off, driven to deep cover, by the right-hander this time
nudged off the back foot towards midwicket
whacked! Makes room by moving towards leg and drives a full ball flat towards the wide long on boundary
short of a length outside off, Deonarine makes room again and cuts the ball hard to the backward point boundary
Milne goes round the wicket and targets the pads at 147kph, Deonarine moves back and nudges off his pad, the ball goes towards the keeper
Deonarine makes room and carves the ball high in the air and it falls safely between point and third man
jumps forward and past leg to hit through the off side but bottom edges towards fine leg
that's short and fast, Deonarine gets under it and slashes, the ball goes off the top edge to the third man boundary
short of a length and slower, Bravo moves outside leg and chips the ball over extra cover, superbly timed
defended back to the bowler
Bravo flicks a full ball off his pads through midwicket

caught at cover point! That appears to be a low catch by Milne. The umpires will check if it carried. It did. Deonarine went back and cut a length ball, it dipped on Milne, who got down low on one knee and just got his fingers under the ball
Ramdin glances the ball off his pads to short fine leg
Bravo tries to flay the ball over cover point but is beaten
tries to cut but gets a bottom edge towards third man
a half-volley outside off and Bravo reaches his fifty by finding the cover boundary with a flowing square drive
flicked from the crease to midwicket
the short ball outside off, left alone by the batsman

Bravo ends the match with a six, getting under a length ball and driving over the cover boundary, there's one final attempt to win $100,000 by a fan diving forward to take a one-handed catch but he too drops it
